The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, July 14, 2004 				 Prisoner choice
																								New Delhi, July 13 (PTI): Death-row prisoners should be allowed to choose the mode of their own execution  either by the hangmans noose or a lethal intravenous injections  recommends the Law Commission of Indias report tabled in Parliament recently by the government.																								The 187th report of the commission, headed by Justice M.J. Rao, was submitted to the NDA government in October 2003 titled Mode of Execution of Death Sentence and Incidental Matters. 
